Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes a new transmission protocol for 5G communication networks that utilizes SDN technology to improve data transmission efficiency. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may also discuss security considerations related to the proposed protocol. 
3. cs.COMM (Computer Communication Networks) - The paper focuses on improving data transmission efficiency between end hosts in a network, which falls under the scope of computer communication networks. 
4. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper may discuss the hardware architecture required to implement the proposed protocol. 
5. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper may discuss the distributed nature of the proposed protocol and its potential for parallel and cluster computing.
